# Primitive Tokens — {{brand.name}}

> Raw color scales derived from the brand's two anchor colors. **Never reference these directly in component code** — use semantic tokens instead.

---

## Primary scale

Derived from `{{palette.primary}}` (brand accent).

| Token | Value | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `--primary-50` | *(computed)* | Tinted backgrounds, hover states on white |
| `--primary-100` | *(computed)* | Subtle tinted surfaces |
| `--primary-200` | *(computed)* | Light fills, decorative borders |
| `--primary-300` | *(computed)* | Disabled states, placeholder fills |
| `--primary-400` | *(computed)* | Secondary brand elements |
| `--primary-500` | `{{palette.primary}}` | Base brand color |
| `--primary-600` | *(computed)* | CTAs, interactive elements (default) |
| `--primary-700` | *(computed)* | Hover state for primary CTA |
| `--primary-800` | *(computed)* | Pressed/active state |
| `--primary-900` | *(computed)* | Deep brand fills |
| `--primary-950` | *(computed)* | Near-deep brand color |

